{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Canvas","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"\n <ol>\n  <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\"><strong>Canvas API</strong></a></li>\n  <li class=\"toggle\">\n    <details open=\"\">\n      <summary>Canvas tutorial</summary>\n      <ol>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Basic_usage\">Basic usage</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Drawing_shapes\">Drawing shapes</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Applying_styles_and_colors\">Applying styles and colors</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Drawing_text\">Drawing text</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Using_images\">Using images</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Transformations\">Transformations</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Compositing\">Compositing and clipping</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Basic_animations\">Basic animations</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Advanced_animations\">Advanced animations</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Pixel_manipulation_with_canvas\">Pixel manipulation</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Optimizing_canvas\">Optimizing the canvas</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Finale\">Finale</a></li>\n        </ol>\n    </details>\n  </li>\n  <li class=\"toggle\">\n    <details open=\"\">\n      <summary>Examples</summary>\n      <ol>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/A_basic_ray-caster\">A basic raycaster</a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Manipulating_video_using_canvas\">Manipulating video using canvas</a></li>\n      </ol>\n    </details>\n  </li>\n  <li class=\"toggle\">\n    <details open=\"\">\n      <summary>Interfaces</summary>\n      <ol>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/HTMLCanvasElement\"><code>HTMLCanvasElement</code></a></li>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D\"><code>CanvasRenderingContext2D</code></a></li>\n        <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasGradient\"><code>CanvasGradient</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n        <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasPattern\"><code>CanvasPattern</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n        <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageBitmap\"><code>ImageBitmap</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n        <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageData\"><code>ImageData</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n        <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextMetrics\"><code>TextMetrics</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n        <li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg> <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Path2D\"><code>Path2D</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n      </ol>\n    </details>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong><a href=\"/de/docs/MDN\">Documentation:</a></strong></li>\n  <li class=\"toggle\">\n    <details>\n      <summary>Contribute</summary>\n      <ol>\n        <li><a href=\"/de/docs/MDN\">The MDN project</a></li>\n      </ol>\n    </details>\n  </li>\n </ol>\n","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div id=\"sect1\"></div>\n\n<p class=\"summary\">Mit der Einführung von <a href=\"/en-US/docs/HTML/HTML5\" class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\">HTML5 </a>wurde ein neues \"Leinwand\" Element zum Zeichnen von Grafiken mittels <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript\">JavaScript</a>-API vorgestellt:&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/HTML/Element/canvas\"><code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code></a></strong>. Die Anwendungsgebiete sind äußerst flexibel, so ist es möglich, mit Canvas Diagramme zu zeichnen, Bilder zu bearbeiten, Animationen zu erstellen oder sogar Videos zu bearbeiten und zu rendern.</p>\n\n<p>Der Support für <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> in Mozilla-Anwendungen wurde ab Gecko 1.8 (sprich ab <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/1.5\">Firefox 1.5</a>) implementiert. Canvas stammt ursprünglich von Apple und wurde für das OS X <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dashboard_%28Mac_OS%29\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Dashboard </a>und den Safari-browser entwickelt. Der Internet Explorer unterstützt Canvas ab Version 9, wobei es durch ein Skript von Google's <a href=\"http://excanvas.sourceforge.net/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Explorer Canvas Projekt</a> auch in früheren Versionen des IE lauffähig ist. Google Chrome und Opera ab Version 9 unterstützen <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> ebenfalls problemlos.</p>\n\n<p>Das <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> Element wird zudem von <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API\">WebGL </a>für die hardwarebeschleunigte Darstellung von 3D-Grafiken auf Webseiten eingesetzt.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"beispiel","title":"Beispiel","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Dies ist ein einfacher Code-Ausschnitt mit der <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D/fillRect\"><code>CanvasRenderingContext2D.fillRect()</code></a> Methode.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"html","title":"HTML","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>canvas</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>canvas<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>canvas</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"javascript","title":"JavaScript","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> canvas <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementById</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"canvas\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> ctx <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> canvas<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getContext</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"2d\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nctx<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>fillStyle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"green\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nctx<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">fillRect</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Bearbeite den untenstehenden Code und sieh live Updates im Canvas: (Funktion kaputt auf Deutsch, die Englische Seite funktioniert, bitte oben umschalten auf Englisch )</p>\n\n<p><iframe class=\"sample-code-frame\" title=\"JavaScript\" id=\"frame_playable_code\" width=\"700\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://yari-demos.prod.mdn.mozit.cloud/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/_sample_.playable_code.html\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"referenzen","title":"Referenzen","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"index\" id=\"sect2\">\n<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/HTMLCanvasElement\"><code>HTMLCanvasElement</code></a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/CanvasRenderingContext2D\"><code>CanvasRenderingContext2D</code></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasGradient\"><code>CanvasGradient</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasPattern\"><code>CanvasPattern</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageBitmap\"><code>ImageBitmap</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ImageData\"><code>ImageData</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextMetrics\"><code>TextMetrics</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li>\n <li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Path2D\"><code>Path2D</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a> <svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<p>Die Schnittstellen, die sich auf <code>WebGLRenderingContext</code> beziehen, werden unter <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API\" title=\"/en-US/docs/Web/WebGL\">WebGL</a> zusammengefasst.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"leitfäden_und_anleitungen","title":"Leitfäden und Anleitungen","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n <dt id=\"canvas_tutorial\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial\">Canvas Tutorial</a></dt>\n <dd>Eine ausführliche Anleitung, die sowohl grundlegende Nutzung als auch fortgeschrittene Funktionen umfasst</dd>\n <dt id=\"code-ausschnitte_canvas\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Add-ons/Code_snippets/Canvas\">Code-Ausschnitte: Canvas</a></dt>\n <dd>Einige Entwickler-orientierte Code-Ausschnitte, die <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code> enthalten.</dd>\n <dt id=\"demo_a_basic_ray-caster\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/A_basic_ray-caster\" class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\">Demo: A basic ray-caster</a></dt>\n <dd>A demo of ray-tracing animation using canvas.</dd>\n <dt id=\"dom-objekte_in_ein_canvas_zeichnen\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Drawing_DOM_objects_into_a_canvas\" class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\">DOM-Objekte in ein canvas zeichnen</a></dt>\n <dd>Wie man DOM Inhalt, wie zum Beispiel HTML-Elemente, in ein canvas zeichnet.</dd>\n <dt id=\"videos_mit_canvas_manipulieren\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Manipulating_video_using_canvas\">Videos mit canvas manipulieren</a></dt>\n <dd><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/HTML/Element/video\"><code>&lt;video&gt;</code></a> und <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/HTML/Element/canvas\"><code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code></a> kombinieren, um Videos in Echtzeit zu manipulieren.</dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"quellen","title":"Quellen","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"allgemeines","title":"Allgemeines","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"https://joshondesign.com/p/books/canvasdeepdive/title.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5 Canvas Deep Dive</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"https://bucephalus.org/text/CanvasHandbook/CanvasHandbook.html\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Canvas Handbook</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"libraries","title":"Libraries","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"http://fabricjs.com\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Fabric.js</a> is an open-source canvas library with SVG parsing capabilities.</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://github.com/ericdrowell/KineticJS\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Kinetic.js</a> is an open-source canvas library focused on interactivity for desktop and mobile applications.</li>\n <li><a href=\"http://paperjs.org/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Paper.js</a> is an open source vector graphics scripting framework that runs on top of the HTML5 Canvas.</li>\n <li><a href=\"http://libcanvas.github.com/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">libCanvas</a> is powerful and lightweight canvas framework.</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://processingjs.org\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Processing.js</a> is a port of the Processing visualization language.</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://playcanvas.com/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">PlayCanvas</a> is an open source game engine.</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://www.pixijs.com/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Pixi.js</a> is an open source game engine.</li>\n <li><a href=\"http://www.liquidx.net/plotkit/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">PlotKit</a> is a charting and graphing library.</li>\n <li><a class=\"link-https external\" href=\"https://github.com/jeremyckahn/rekapi\" rel=\" noopener\">Rekapi</a> is an animation key-framing API for Canvas.</li>\n <li><a href=\"http://senchalabs.github.com/philogl/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">PhiloGL</a> is a WebGL framework for data visualization, creative coding and game development.</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://thejit.org/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">JavaScript InfoVis Toolkit</a> creates interactive 2D Canvas data visualizations for the Web.</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"spezifikationen","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <thead>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n </thead>\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/the-canvas-element.html\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML Living Standard<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'Canvas' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-living\">Lebender Standard</span></td>\n   <td>&nbsp;</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebGL_API\">WebGL</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Beispiel","id":"beispiel"},{"text":"Referenzen","id":"referenzen"},{"text":"Leitfäden und Anleitungen","id":"leitfäden_und_anleitungen"},{"text":"Quellen","id":"quellen"},{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"spezifikationen"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Mit der Einführung von HTML5 wurde ein neues \"Leinwand\" Element zum Zeichnen von Grafiken mittels JavaScript-API vorgestellt: <canvas>. Die Anwendungsgebiete sind äußerst flexibel, so ist es möglich, mit Canvas Diagramme zu zeichnen, Bilder zu bearbeiten, Animationen zu erstellen oder sogar Videos zu bearbeiten und zu rendern.","popularity":0.0006,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Canvas API","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"API Canvas","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"API canvas","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"キャンバス API","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Canvas API","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Canvas","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Canvas API","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/api/canvas_api","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/api/canvas_api/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Web","title":"Webtechnologien für Entwickler"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/API","title":"Web API Referenz"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API","title":"Canvas"}],"pageTitle":"Canvas - Web API Referenz | MDN","noIndexing":false}}